snippet.textDisplay: I was shocked and saddened when I heard about Kobe Bryant, but not blowing it all out of proportion. He was a talented but flawed human being like the rest of us. He was nothing more special than the next door neighbor. Every life and death are pretty much equal but sadly not celebrated and mourned equally. The police like to do the same thing when they lose one their own. They act as if a cop's death is more special than Joe Blow's death. It's not. Neither is Bryant's. Let us all mourn every death and celebrate every life equally. (as much as is humanly possible).
